# CI/CD (GitHub Actions)

See [docs/cicd.md](../../docs/cicd.md) for setup checklist and ADO mapping.

## Secrets vs variables

**Use GitHub variables (`vars.*`)** for non-sensitive configuration: resource names, public usernames, subscription IDs, client IDs, tenant IDs, image repository names passed as workflow inputs.

**Use GitHub secrets (`secrets.*`)** only for credentials: tokens, passwords, deployment keys (Docker Hub token, SWA deploy token, etc.).

Reusable workflows:

- Pass non-secrets via `workflow_call` **inputs** or read **`vars`** in the called workflow (e.g. `vars.DOCKERHUB_USERNAME` at repo level; environment-scoped vars on jobs with `environment: test`).
- Pass credentials via `workflow_call` **secrets** only — never put secrets in `with:` inputs.

## Naming convention

Use **UPPER_SNAKE_CASE**. Prefer descriptive segments over abbreviating the environment to `TEST`/`PROD` at the start of the name.

**Azure and other cloud resources** (variables and secrets):

```
[SERVICEPROVIDER]_[SERVICETYPE]_[WORKLOADNAME]_[DESCRIPTION]_[TARGETENV]
```

| Segment | Meaning | Examples |
|---------|---------|----------|
| Service provider | Vendor / platform | `AZURE`, `DOCKERHUB` |
| Service type | Azure resource or product | `WEBAPP`, `FUNCTIONAPP`, `STATICWEBAPP`, `ENTRA`, `SUBSCRIPTION` |
| Workload name | Monorepo app or role | `API`, `FUNCTIONS`, `WEB`, `APP`, `OIDC`, `DEPLOY` |
| Description | What the value holds | `RESOURCENAME`, `DEPLOYTOKEN`, `CLIENTID`, `SUBSCRIPTIONID` |
| Target env | ADO/Azure stage suffix | `STG` (GitHub `test`), `PRD` (GitHub `prod`) |

Examples:

| Kind | Name |
|------|------|
| Variable | `AZURE_WEBAPP_API_RESOURCENAME_STG` |
| Variable | `AZURE_FUNCTIONAPP_FUNCTIONS_RESOURCENAME_STG` |
| Variable | `AZURE_ENTRA_OIDC_CLIENTID_STG` |
| Secret | `AZURE_STATICWEBAPP_WEB_DEPLOYTOKEN_STG` |
| Secret | `DOCKERHUB_TOKEN` |

**Third-party accounts** that are not environment-specific may use a shorter `[PROVIDER]_[DESCRIPTION]` form (no target env suffix):

| Kind | Name |
|------|------|
| Variable | `DOCKERHUB_USERNAME` |
| Secret | `DOCKERHUB_TOKEN` |

Store environment-specific Azure values on the matching GitHub Environment (`test` → `*_STG`, `prod` → `*_PRD`) even when the suffix repeats the environment name — it keeps names self-describing in workflow YAML and logs.

## Layout

- `*-ci.yml` — build/test on PR and `develop`/`main`
- `*-cd.yml` — deploy to `test` on `main` only; merge Docker publish + Azure deploy per app
- `reusable/` — shared deploy and Docker push templates; accept `environment` input (`test` \| `prod`)

## Agent access to GitHub

Configure GitHub MCP for Actions triage and PR creation — see [docs/github-mcp-setup.md](../../docs/github-mcp-setup.md). PAT needs **Pull requests: Read and write**; omit `X-MCP-Readonly` in `.cursor/mcp.json`.
